The course gives an overview of the subject, main directions, methods, databases and concepts of general linguistics is given, as well as the connections of linguistics with related sciences. During the course, the student writes his linguistic biography, which is the subject's exam paper. The wiki environment supports the student in the course: https://wiki.ilonatragel.ut.ee/w/index.php?title=EsilehtObjectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the subject is to provide an introduction to all linguistic subjects, to introduce the basic topics and concepts of linguistics.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon finishing this course, the student orients himself in the main directions of linguistics and the structure of the language, knows the terms necessary for reading linguistic literature in Estonian, knows how to search for the linguistic materials he needs and connect his language experience with them.
